BUCHAREST, Romania -- Interior Minister Vasile Blaga and French Minister of Home Affairs Dominique de Villepin sealed a protocol Monday (10 January) intensifying co-operation in the fight against organised crime.
This was the first visit paid by a senior Western official to Romania since elections last month.
During his one-day visit to Bucharest, de Villepin also met with President Traian Basescu and Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu.
(Nine o'clock, Rompres - 11/01/05)
